{"source_key":"sha256-ea08d35f42d5530fbe92c80d4f5b27e9","record_index":514,"record_hash":"sha256:1f3dfe703eb1bb66670ba6989c27d58eb123a4275c9345dc9d28d77e05052101","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:39:57.462Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: agent-trail.md\n@@\n Pierre/code.storage should be considered a remote caching and Git hosting layer,\n not a replacement for local GitMeta materialization in v1. The current\n `git-meta-lib` entry point is path/repository based: `Session::open(path)` opens\n a `gix::Repository`, creates or reads `.git/git-meta.sqlite`, fetches/materializes\n metadata refs into that local store, and reads values through\n `SessionTargetHandle`. `but-agentlog` currently depends on that shape.\n \n That means Agent Trail still needs a server-side scratch/cache Git repository\n with filesystem access before calling the NAPI projection API. The NAPI request\n should pass a local `repoPath`, not raw remote bytes.\n+\n+Pierre does not currently make a remote repository appear as a mounted local\n+repository to the server process. It gives Forge Git hosting/API/proxy\n+capabilities. To make `git-meta-lib` happy, Forge still has to materialize a\n+real local Git repository/object database/ref namespace on disk, even if the\n+remote it fetches from is Pierre/code.storage.\n \n Pierre may still be useful in front of that local repository:\n@@\n Do not parse GitMeta trees directly from code.storage file APIs in Forge for\n v1. That would duplicate `git-meta-lib` materialization and `but-agentlog`\n storage interpretation. A future lower-level `git-meta-lib` API could accept an\n explicit object database or in-memory GitMeta source, but that is a separate\n library-design project.\n+\n+If Forge's deployment target cannot provide a writable cache directory, `git`,\n+native addon loading, and enough request/worker time to fetch and materialize\n+GitMeta, do not force Agent Trail generation into this Next.js app. Split the\n+generator into a separate service or worker with durable local storage and have\n+Forge call it over HTTP or a queue. Forge can still own the public routes and UI,\n+but the repository cache and projection generation should live where the runtime\n+fits the workload.\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:39:57.462Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}